article.headline: Cal State Northridge 67, UC Irvine 61
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Rob Haynes and Jonathan Heard's 11-point run in the second half lifted Cal State Northridge to a 67-61 Big West Conference victory over UC Irvine Thursday. Northridge (8-7, 2-2 Big West Conference) trailed 53-51 with 5 minutes, 33 seconds remaining before Haynes made a field goal. Heard scored six points in a row and Haynes made a 3-pointer to take a 62-53 lead with 2:40 to play. Haynes scored a game-high 16 points off the bench and Heard scored 14 points and took a game-high seven rebounds. UC Irvine (7-10, 1-2) trailed 47-29 with 14:26 remaining before going on a 24-4 run and taking a 53-51 lead. After giving up 11 consecutive points, the Anteaters scored seven in a row, including five by Adam Templeton to cut the Matadors lead to 62-60 with 52.5 seconds to play. Northridge's Calvin Chitwood rebounded a Marcus McIntosh miss and made two free throws on the other end to build the lead to 64-60 with 26.4 seconds remaining. After McIntosh made one free throw with 17.6 seconds remaining, Jason Hill made four free throws for the final margin. Rai Colston added 11 points for Northridge. Darren Fells's 11 points was the only Anteater to score in double figures.
